FBIS4-16923 "drsov076_f_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-076 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 National Affairs Chernobyl Safety Switches on After `Accident' Chernobyl Safety Switches on After `Accident' LD1904192094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1840 GMT 19 Apr 94 LD1904192094 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent] [Text] Kiev April 19 TASS -- The safety system switched on in the third power unit of the Chernobyl nuclear power plant, Ukraine, during Monday's increase of the unit capacity after the planned repairs. A reason for this was the lowered water level in hydroballoons of the reactor's emergency cooling system. The accident is estimated as the first level (the international scale) and does not endanger the plant's personnel or safe operation of the facility.
